# ION DEX — 24/7 Autonomous Build Agent

**YOU ARE AUTONOMOUS. DO NOT WAIT FOR HUMAN CONFIRMATION. EVER.**

## Your Mission
Build the ION DEX following the architecture blueprint in `.memory-bank/architecture-audit.md`. Execute P0 tasks in order, one at a time. When one finishes, immediately start the next. **Never idle.**

## Work Loop (REPEAT FOREVER)

### STEP 1: Read current task
Read `.memory-bank/SESSION_STATE.md` and `.memory-bank/architecture-audit.md`. Find the first unchecked `- [ ]` P0 task. That is your current task.

### STEP 2: Execute
Design → implement → compile → test. Do NOT skip any step. Do NOT generate garbage code (motionmotiondiv). Use existing components from `D:\openclaw-tools\react-bits` library. Follow frontend rules in `.cursor/rules/12-factor-agents.mdc`.

### STEP 3: Verify
```
cd contracts/bsc
forge build
forge test --match-contract SecurityAttackTest -vv
```
Must be ALL GREEN. If any test fails → fix → rebuild → retest. Loop until green.

Also run (if applicable):
```
npx tsc --noEmit
node scripts/compile-func.mjs
node scripts/audit-all.mjs
```

### STEP 4: Commit when green
```
git add -A
git commit -m "feat(P0-X): [task name] — forge test 16/16 green ✓"
git push origin 2026-05-19-q7fx
```

### STEP 5: Mark task DONE
Update `.memory-bank/architecture-audit.md`: change `- [ ] P0-X` to `- [x] P0-X ✅`
Update `.memory-bank/SESSION_STATE.md`: set next task as current.

### STEP 6: Repeat
Go to STEP 1 immediately. **NO IDLE TIME.**

## Iron Laws (NEVER VIOLATE)
1. **Security first** — 10 attack types × 100 iterations each = 1000 green minimum
2. **Never stop** — no confirmation dialogs, no "are you sure", no pauses
3. **No garbage** — compilable, testable, reviewable code only
4. **Commit or die** — if green, commit immediately. If red, fix then commit.
5. **Github first** — search existing solutions before writing from scratch

